ingredients: 1 box (4.7 oz) Old El Paso® Stand 'N Stuff® taco shells (10 shells)
3 cups cut-up deli rotisserie chicken (from 2- to 2 1/2-lb chicken)
1 package (1 oz) Old El Paso® taco seasoning mix
1/4 cup sliced green onions (4 medium), if desired Old El Paso® Thick 'n Chunky salsa, if desired Additional ranch dressing, if desired
1372280272.name: Chicken Ranch Tacos
1372280272.procedure: Heat oven to 325°F. Heat taco shells in oven as directed on box. Meanwhile, in medium microwavable bowl, place chicken. Sprinkle with taco seasoning mix; toss gently to coat. Microwave uncovered on High 2 to 3 minutes or until hot. Stir in 1/2 cup dressing. Spoon warm chicken mixture into heated taco shells. Top with lettuce, tomato, cheese and onions. Drizzle with salsa and additional dressing.

1372269818.name: Bombay Chicken Wings
1372269818.procedure:
Combine chicken wings, vegetable oil, soy sauce, green onion, garlic, curry powder, turmeric, and black pepper in a resealable plastic bag. Squeeze out the air, seal bag, and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
Spread chicken wings into a large baking dish.
Bake in the preheated oven until wings are browned, about 25 minutes.
